'''Marie Louise Lydia Elisabeth "Marlies" Veldhuijzen van Zanten-Hyllner''' (born 29 September 1953 in [[Gothenburg]], Sweden) is a former [[Netherlands|Dutch]] politician of the [[Christian Democratic Appeal]] (CDA). She was the [[State Secretary (Netherlands)|State Secretary]] for [[Ministry of Health, Welfare and Sport (Netherlands)|Health, Welfare and Sport]] in the [[first Rutte cabinet]], serving from 14 October 2010 to 5 November 2012.<ref>{{nl icon}} [http://www.cda.nl/Onze_mensen/Per_organisatie/Kabinet/Onze_mensen/Marlies_Veldhuijzen_van_Zanten-Hyllner.aspx Marlies Veldhuijzen van Zanten-Hyllner] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120312142219/http://www.cda.nl/Onze_mensen/Per_organisatie/Kabinet/Onze_mensen/Marlies_Veldhuijzen_van_Zanten-Hyllner.aspx |date=2012-03-12 }} ''[[Christian Democratic Appeal]]''</ref>
